sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: FLAG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a FLAG tag octapeptide special internal domain designed to be internal to the sequence of a protein. FLAG tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The FLAG sequence AspTyrLysAspAspAspAspLys (DYKDDDDK) is one of the most commonly used FLAG tag sequences. Each of the amino acids in this octapeptide have two possible codon choices. For each amino acid, neither of the two codon choices appear to be rare in the common model organisms. So codons were selected to minimize repeats.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a HA tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. HA tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This domain encodes the HA sequence YPYDVPDYA. The codons at each amino acid position were selected to avoid rare codons as much as possible in organisms like ''E. coli'', humans, mouse, ''B. subtilis'', ''C. elegans'', ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' and other common model organisms and/or industrial hosts. Another factor in codon selection was avoiding avoid repeat sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70620
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RFC12 Maltose Binding Protein Internal Domain [malE]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Joseph Lynch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This Maltose-binding protein is designed for either N-terminal or C-terminal fusions. MBP fused proteins can be purified in one step affinity chromatography using a cross-linked amylose matrix and then eluted with 10 mM maltose. Note that the amylose matrix can only be regenerated, in most cases, up to five times. The large size of this tag can also affect the fused protein.
MBP fusions often have higher levels of expression and solubility that the native untagged protein, with typical yields of up to 40 mg/liter culture.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Primers:

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Vector containing Hisx6 and Sortase tag LPETGG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sigrun Stulz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This vector is constructed to simplify the usage of the transpeptidase Sortase A for future iGEM teams. Following a BamHI restriction site we constructed a synthetic sequence consisting of three main elements: 1) A linker (GSSS) to allow for limited mobility of the attached peptides and facilitate correct folding 2) A Sortase A tag (LPETGG) that is used to conjugate the proteins to poly-glycines 3) A standard Hisx6 tag commonly used for Immobilized Metal Affinity Chromatography (IMAC)
This sequence follows a BamHI restriction site which can be used by teams to clone in whichever peptide they would like to conjugate using Sortase A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BamHI is a very convenient restriction enzyme for our application as its restriction site will code for a glycine and a serine, both of which are often used in linkers and tend to be unproblematic in such sequences.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The plasmid was constructed using the iGEM-supplied pSB1C3 and a synthetically produced sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: FLAG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sara Mouradian
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the polypeptide protein FLAG tag. It is used in antibody binding assays if there is no antibody against the studied protein. It should be put at either the N terminus or the C terminus of the protein This part uses the modified Silver BioBrick prefix and suffix to allow for protein construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Tags are almost always used in conjunction with another protein (the one being studied), so we used the modified Silver BioBrick prefix and suffix to make the construction of funcitonal fusion peptides possible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is easily recognized by many antibodies.
